WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.546 --> 00:00:09.645
Important: all data in this demo is public-facing — nothing confidential is shown.

2
00:00:09.645 --> 00:00:18.536
This is Pfizer Digital Analytics from Vibe Code Flow, giving communications teams a unified view of corporate and executive social performance.

3
00:00:19.436 --> 00:00:31.246
The all-channels view rolls up Pfizer's social performance — followers, posts, engagement, reach, and impressions across LinkedIn, X, Instagram, Facebook, YouTube, and TikTok.

4
00:00:32.146 --> 00:00:35.606
On LinkedIn, every post gets a full qualitative breakdown.

5
00:00:35.606 --> 00:00:38.231
What Worked explains why the content landed.

6
00:00:38.231 --> 00:00:43.182
Improvements flags what's holding engagement back, with specific suggested changes.

7
00:00:43.182 --> 00:00:54.516
Narrative Role shows where each post fits in Pfizer's corporate story arc — and those action recommendations translate directly into updates for your digital strategy and quarterly planning.

8
00:00:55.416 --> 00:01:04.846
Each platform gets the same treatment — channel KPIs, story-beat breakdowns, and post-level scoring for X, Instagram, YouTube, and TikTok.

9
00:01:05.746 --> 00:01:15.326
The weekly report compares this week against last week and maps posts onto a narrative arc — so you can see whether Pfizer is building story momentum or publishing in isolation.

10
00:01:16.226 --> 00:01:26.066
Monthly reporting rolls up post performance across every channel with a direct comparison to the prior month, surfacing top performers and posts that need a strategy reset.

11
00:01:26.966 --> 00:01:40.786
The quarterly one-pager connects post-level insights to Strategic Recommendations — concrete actions on content mix, paid support, and competitor gaps that leadership can use to update Pfizer's digital strategy and resource plans for the next quarter.

12
00:01:41.686 --> 00:01:50.206
Switch to CEO analytics for Albert Bourla's personal LinkedIn and X presence — the same scoring engine, tuned for executive communications.

13
00:01:51.106 --> 00:01:59.936
Review individual CEO posts with deep-dive analysis: engagement, narrative role, and specific recommendations for the executive voice.

14
00:02:00.836 --> 00:02:08.656
The CEO's X channel gets the same post-level scoring and narrative insights, keeping executive social performance in one place.

15
00:02:09.556 --> 00:02:14.829
Wikipedia is critical because it ranks at the top of Google and other search engines.

16
00:02:14.829 --> 00:02:22.149
When investors, journalists, or employees search for Pfizer, the Wikipedia article is often the first link they click.

17
00:02:22.149 --> 00:02:27.298
This view tracks pageview trends, maintenance flags, and editorial recommendations.

18
00:02:27.298 --> 00:02:33.501
Important: Wikipedia is an open-source platform — it cannot be updated or edited by Pfizer directly.

19
00:02:33.501 --> 00:02:37.657
Changes must come from the volunteer community that runs Wikipedia.

20
00:02:37.657 --> 00:02:46.156
For additional insights and strategy regarding your presence on Wikipedia, please contact Vibe Code Flow for more information and advice.

21
00:02:47.056 --> 00:02:53.862
The same applies to executive profiles — Albert Bourla's Wikipedia page shapes first impressions in search results.

22
00:02:53.862 --> 00:02:59.899
As with the corporate article, only the Wikipedia community can edit the page, not the company itself.

23
00:02:59.899 --> 00:03:05.876
Vibe Code Flow can help you interpret these signals and plan the right community engagement strategy.
24
00:03:05.900 --> 00:03:08.367
Thank you for watching.

25
